From: EDORP maintainers <edohikmahtiar@me.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Make pypdfium2 optional for extraction-only builds

MarkItDown uses pdfplumber's text, word, and table extraction APIs, none of
which need PDFium.  Keep rendering unavailable with an explicit diagnostic
instead of imposing a bundled PDFium binary on extraction-only installations.

--- a/pdfplumber/display.py
+++ b/pdfplumber/display.py
@@ -7 +7,4 @@
-import pypdfium2  # type: ignore
+try:
+    import pypdfium2  # type: ignore
+except ImportError:
+    pypdfium2 = None  # type: ignore
@@ -43,0 +47,5 @@
+    if pypdfium2 is None:
+        raise ModuleNotFoundError(
+            "PDF rendering is unavailable in this extraction-only build; "
+            "install pypdfium2 to use Page.to_image()"
+        )
--- a/requirements.txt
+++ b/requirements.txt
@@ -3 +2,0 @@
-pypdfium2>=5.9.0
